UNITED STATES of America v. ONE 1941 FORD DELUXE COACH, MOTOR NO. 18—6,063,372, and First National Bank & Trust Company of Oklahoma City, Oklahoma. No. 2382. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Sept. 8, 1941. Tom Hieronymus, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Oklahoma City, Okl., for appellant. No appearance for appellees.

Before PHILLIPS, BRATTON, and HUXMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on motion of appellant.
